text.value: Cystic Fibrosis DNA result: Positive for one pathogenic mutation: 3120+1G>A Interpretation: This individual is heterozygous for the 3120+1G>A (c.2988+1G>A) mutation in the CFTR gene. This result does not rule out the possibility that this individual is affected with cystic fibrosis. Clinical follow up is recommended. Method: DNA isolated from dried blood spot specimen undergoes CFTR mutation detection assay using Luminex xTAG Cystic Fibrosis v2 (CF60) v.02. ACTION: SWEAT CHLORIDE TESTING AND GENETIC COUNSELING RECOMMENDED.

text.value: Phenylketonuria (PKU) DNA Result: Positive for two pathogenic mutations: c.1222C>T/c.473G>A Interpretation: This individual has two mutations, c.1222C>T and c.473G>A, in the PAH gene. This result is consistent with the clinical diagnosis of Phenylketonuria. Method: DNA isolated from dried blood spot specimen undergoes targeted gene sequencing analysis. ACTION: REFERRAL TO METABOLIC SPECIALIST FOR DIAGNOSTIC TESTING.
